#note I'm blocking random bingos Tim might have if he has the case S, and also reaching into the bag to try to pick up the Z. It's going to be a tough road to win from here, especially after I block the bingo lane - basically just a siege. Since I'm an underdog (about 40% to win) I might want to leave column M open. Q likes AUTO at O12, I think because it blocks cheap MIZ/MOZ/MEZE plays.
>Tim: EENNRUZ M12 .EZE +48 323
>Jesse: AAINOOV 6J VIN.A +20 305
#note it did not look good. I wish I'd been savvy enough to block the Z spot. the alternative here is OVONIC, but I thought it would end the game too fast. I'm trying to turn over tiles and draw AH/EDH.
>Tim: NNPRSUW 14M ..P +14 337
#note I think this is a great block!
>Jesse: AEIOOPR 14D POI +21 326
#note I have a killer move here of PRONAOI at L3, which could win if he has an awkward rack (he is often tight on vowels). With POI my only real path to victory is going out first, which is going to be hard to pull off. With Tim's actual rack, I would've been 3/8 to win. The H is a key tile here even after EDH gets blocked, and PRONAOI gives me a better chance of drawing it. Also, just in terms of tempo, I can choose to be down 2 with 1 tile left in the bag, versus 11+the value of Tim's next turn, so PRONAOI is a no-brainer.
